**Celanese Corp.: A Chemical Industry Leader Experiencing Steady Growth**

In the 2024 Fortune ranking, Celanese Corp. secured the 369th position, marking a notable 27-spot improvement from its previous year's ranking. The Irving, Texas-based chemicals company, led by CEO Lori J. Ryerkerk, demonstrates a resilient performance amidst a competitive industry landscape.

Founded in 1918, Celanese has evolved into a prominent player in the global chemicals sector, boasting a diverse portfolio of products catering to various industries. The company's commitment to innovation and strategic growth initiatives has contributed to its steady ascent in the rankings.

As a profitable entity, Celanese reported revenues of $10,940 million for the year, representing a 13.1% increase from the previous year. This upward trend is further reinforced by the company's 3.5% growth in profits, which totaled $1,960 million. The company's total assets stood at $26,597 million, underscoring its solid financial foundation.

Celanese's market capitalization as of March 28, 2024, was valued at $19,173.3 million, demonstrating its significant presence in the global market. The company's publicly traded status and strong market performance make it an attractive investment opportunity for stakeholders.

Under the leadership of CEO Lori J. Ryerkerk, the company continues to navigate the complexities of the chemicals industry. As one of the few female CEOs in the sector, Ryerkerk's guidance has been instrumental in driving Celanese's growth strategy and fostering a culture of innovation within the organization.

With a workforce of 12,410 employees, Celanese maintains a substantial presence in the global chemicals industry. Although the company did not experience growth in jobs, its stable employment base is a testament to its commitment to its workforce.

Celanese's ranking improvement is a reflection of its adaptability and responsiveness to market demands. While the company did not feature in the Global 500, World's Most Admired Companies, or Best Companies to Work For lists, its steady growth and solid financial performance position it as a formidable player in the chemicals sector.

As the company continues to navigate the evolving landscape of the chemicals industry, its strong leadership, diversified product portfolio, and commitment to innovation will likely contribute to its sustained growth and success in the years to come.